{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "This is a PR to remove more of boost from sdformat.  This PR is mostly concerned with replacing uses of boost::filesystem in the library.\r\n\r\nThere are 2 potential problems with this PR that I would like to discuss:\r\n\r\n1. If you look closely at Filesystem.cc, most of the Windows code is lifted directly from boost/libs/filesystem, then adapted to fit the sdformat style (along with various other fixes).  I'm not sure how the licensing works in this case; how do we proceed here?\r\n1. There are no tests for Filesystem.cc.  The main reason for this is that I am missing portable versions of some primitives I would need to have reliable tests (change directory, remove directory, etc).  Should I spend time porting those primitives from boost, even though we don't use them in the main code?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This is a PR to remove more of boost from sdformat.  This PR is mostly concerned with replacing uses of boost::filesystem in the library.</p>\n<p>There are 2 potential problems with this PR that I would like to discuss:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>If you look closely at Filesystem.cc, most of the Windows code is lifted directly from boost/libs/filesystem, then adapted to fit the sdformat style (along with various other fixes).  I'm not sure how the licensing works in this case; how do we proceed here?</li>\n<li>There are no tests for Filesystem.cc.  The main reason for this is that I am missing portable versions of some primitives I would need to have reliable tests (change directory, remove directory, etc).  Should I spend time porting those primitives from boost, even though we don't use them in the main code?</li>\n</ol>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Remove boost 11", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Remove boost 11</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "This is a PR to remove more of boost from sdformat.  This PR is mostly concerned with replacing uses of boost::filesystem in the library.\r\n\r\nThere are 2 potential problems with this PR that I would like to discuss:\r\n\r\n1. If you look closely at Filesystem.cc, most of the Windows code is lifted directly from boost/libs/filesystem, then adapted to fit the sdformat style (along with various other fixes).  I'm not sure how the licensing works in this case; how do we proceed here?\r\n1. There are no tests for Filesystem.cc.  The main reason for this is that I am missing portable versions of some primitives I would need to have reliable tests (change directory, remove directory, etc).  Should I spend time porting those primitives from boost, even though we don't use them in the main code?", "links": {"decline": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/decline"}, "diffstat": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/sdformat/diffstat/osrf/sdformat:6ce28631a6e3%0D6b84a7ae5505?from_pullrequest_id=335"}, "commits": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/commits.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments_page=1.json"}, "merge": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/merge"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}, "activity": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/activity.json"}, "diff": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/sdformat/diff/osrf/sdformat:6ce28631a6e3%0D6b84a7ae5505?from_pullrequest_id=335"}, "approve": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/approve"}, "statuses": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/statuses_page=1.json"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11", "close_source_branch": true, "reviewers": [{"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitb