o fit the sdformat style (along with various other fixes).  I'm not sure how the licensing works in this case; how do we proceed here?</li>\n<li>There are no tests for Filesystem.cc.  The main reason for this is that I am missing portable versions of some primitives I would need to have reliable tests (change directory, remove directory, etc).  Should I spend time porting those primitives from boost, even though we don't use them in the main code?</li>\n</ol>", "type": "rendered"}, "source": {"commit": {"hash": "e15f3e50b0bc", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/commit/e15f3e50b0bc.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/commits/e15f3e50b0bc"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}ts=1606789"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "sdformat", "full_name": "osrf/sdformat", "uuid": "{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}"}, "branch": {"name": "remove-boost-11"}}, "comment_count": 42, "state": "MERGED", "task_count": 0, "participants": [{"role": "PARTICIPANT", "participated_on": "2017-04-24T17:27:09.448592+00:00", "type": "participant", "approved": false, "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}}, {"role": "PARTICIPANT", "participated_on": "2017-04-24T17:13:32.600616+00:00", "type": "participant", "approved": false, "user": {"display_name"